Federal Realty Investment Trust isissuing a 75 mln dlr convertible eurobond due April 30, 2002paying an indicated coupon of 5-1/4 to 5-1/2 pct and priced atpar, lead manager Salomon Brothers International said.    The issue has a put option after seven years which will bepriced to give the investor a yield in line with current sevenyear U.S. Treasury bond. Final terms will be fixed on April 9.    The selling concession is 1-1/2 pct while management andunderwriting each pay 1/2 pct. The issue is available indenominations of 1,000 and 10,000 dlrs. REUTER&#3;